100 REM === D3 IMAGE: SMALLINT>><, TRUE/FALSE>>IFTRUE:IFFALSE: =====
105 REM SELECTOR IDS:  < = 4, IFTRUE:IFFALSE: = 9.
106 REM CLASS IDS:     SMALLINTEGER = 2, TRUE = 3, FALSE = 4.
107 REM IFTRUE:IFFALSE: TAKES TWO ARGS; EACH METHOD JUST RETURNS THE
108 REM ONE THAT MATCHES ITS RECEIVER CLASS, WITHOUT EVALUATING THE
109 REM OTHER (THE BLOCKS ARE EVALUATED EAGERLY BY THE TOP-LEVEL
110 REM CALLER, SO IN V0 THIS IS A LOOKUP, NOT A LAZY DECISION).
115 GOSUB 10100
120 GOSUB 10700
125 REM SMALLINTEGER>>< AT 512..514:  PRIMITIVE 4 ; RETURN_TOP
130 POKE 512,13
131 POKE 513,4
132 POKE 514,8
133 LET C=2
134 LET G=4
135 LET A=512
136 LET B=3
137 GOSUB 10300
140 REM TRUE>>IFTRUE:IFFALSE: AT 515..517:  PUSH_TEMP 0 ; RETURN_TOP
145 POKE 515,3
146 POKE 516,0
147 POKE 517,8
148 LET C=3
149 LET G=9
150 LET A=515
151 LET B=3
152 GOSUB 10300
155 REM FALSE>>IFTRUE:IFFALSE: AT 518..520: PUSH_TEMP 1 ; RETURN_TOP
160 POKE 518,3
161 POKE 519,1
162 POKE 520,8
163 LET C=4
164 LET G=9
165 LET A=518
166 LET B=3
167 GOSUB 10300
199 RETURN
